author: hwright
msg: libsvn_subr: Use a new filename instead of retrying when opening a unique
temporary file fails on Windows. This removes unneeded extra delays on
naming collisions. (Not only on directories, but also on in-use files).
Wait loops are evil. Especially if they are not usefull, like on naming

Tweak implementations to expect relative paths.
